description: This table presents the performance comparison of the Partition Refinement Search algorithm and the baseline RCompliant method across four different problem domains. caption: Table 1: Expected cost (E) and percent goal achievement rate (% Goal) of Partition Refinement Search and RConfidence on the Lane Merger, Graph Rock Sample, Spaceship Repair, and Store Visit problems. The performance was measured over ten runs to calculate the performance average and standard deviation.
description: This table presents the results of the empirical evaluation of the proposed Partition Refinement Search (PRS) algorithm and a baseline method (RCompliant) across four different problem domains: Lane Merger, Graph Rock Sample, Spaceship Repair, and Store Visit.  For each algorithm and problem, the table shows the average expected cost (Eπ) and the percentage of times the goal was achieved (% Goal). The results are based on ten independent runs, with standard deviations included to represent the variability in performance.
